RT  Systematic genetic nomenclature for type VII secretion systems.
RA  Bitter W, Houben EN, Bottai D, Brodin P, Brown EJ, Cox JS, Derbyshire
RA  K, Fortune SM, Gao LY, Liu J, Gey van Pittius NC, Pym AS, Rubin EJ,
RA  Sherman DR, Cole ST, Brosch R;
RL  PLoS Pathog. 2009;5:e1000507.
CC  Type VII secretion (T7S) is also called ESAT-6-, SNM-, and
CC  ESX-secretion. It occurs in Mycobacterium, which has an impermeable
CC  cell envelope that contains long-chain mycolic acids in an outer
CC  membrane, and T7S provides a means to transport proteins through this
CC  barrier. Multiple T7S loci can occur in one species, with different
CC  secretion targets for different systems. The system includes a
CC  subtilisin-like protease called mycosin and membrane proteins with a
CC  new nomenclature in starting with ecc (esx conserved component).
**  GO:0009306 is general.  Type VII go terms (transport, complex) not yet
**  available.  EccC not built yet because fusion protein gets split. 
**  Additional secreted proteins include Rv3616c, Rv3881c, Rv3615c, Rv3864,
**  Rv3865
